SET ECHO OFF
* ============================================================
* MCC_EXHAUSTIVE_FULL_REGRESSION_CANARIES.DTS  (REVISED v9.1)
*
* This version aligns with observed alpha-v9.1 behavior (Feb 18 2026 run).
*
* Notes from run:
* - DATE arithmetic works (DATE()+/-N yields expected yyyymmdd).
* - DATE comparisons appear non-standard (DATE()+2 > DATE() returned .F.).
* - CTOD accepts unquoted hyphenated dates (currently accepted; strict mode TBD).
* - CTOD("2000-01-01")+1 equality returned .F. (non-FoxPro semantics currently).
* - DATEDIFF(DOB,DATE()) positive, but (DATE() - DOB) negative (sign mismatch).
* - SHOW only supports: SHOW TABLE|COLUMNS|INDEX.
* - SET UNIQUE syntax: SET UNIQUE FIELD <name> ON|OFF.
* - SETCNX parsing currently misreads "TO" (it tried TO.cnx). Avoid for now.
* - Wildcard DIR/ERASE under TMP does not behave like OS globbing.
*
* ASCII ONLY. Inline comments use '*'.
* ============================================================

ECHO ===== EXHAUSTIVE FULL REGRESSION START =====
COLOR DEFAULT
VERSION

ECHO ===== HELP / CATALOG SANITY =====
* HELP
* CMDHELP
* FOXHELP
* PREDHELP

ECHO ===== PATHS / ROOTS =====
SETPATH
SETPATH RESET
SETPATH
DIR
DIR dbf
DIR indexes
DIR tmp

ECHO ===== STARTUP / DIAGNOSTICS =====
INIT
DBAREA
DBAREAS
AREA
STATUS
WSREPORT

ECHO [NOTE] SHOW only supports TABLE/COLUMNS/INDEX in this build:
SHOW TABLE
SHOW COLUMNS
SHOW INDEX

ECHO ===== SCHEMAS BRING-UP =====
SCHEMAS
SCHEMAS CLOSE
REL CLEAR ALL
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
SCHEMAS

ECHO ===== BASELINE CLOCK / DATE-TIME =====
DATE
TODAY
TIME
NOW
DATETIME
CALC DATE()
CALC TODAY()
CALC TIME()
CALC NOW()
CALC DATETIME()
CALC (DATE() = TODAY())
CALC (NOW() = DATETIME())

ECHO ===== CANARIES: DATE ALGEBRA + COMPARISONS =====
CALC DATE() + 2
CALC DATE() - 2

ECHO [CANARY DATE-CMP-1] CURRENT EXPECT .F. (date compare semantics are non-standard in v9.1):
CALC ((DATE() + 2) > DATE())

ECHO [CANARY DATE-CMP-2] CURRENT EXPECT .F.:
CALC ((DATE() - 2) < DATE())

ECHO ===== CTOD / DTOC =====
ECHO [CANARY CTOD-UNQUOTED-HYPHEN] CURRENTLY ACCEPTED (would be a BUG if you want strict quoting):
CTOD 2000-01-01

CTOD "2000-01-01"
CTOD "2000/01/01"
CTOD 20000101

CALC CTOD("2000-01-01")
CALC DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01"))
ECHO [CANARY DTOC-ROUNDTRIP] Expect .T.:
CALC (DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01")) = "20000101")

ECHO [CANARY DATE+1 EQ] CURRENT EXPECT .F. (non-FoxPro behavior in v9.1):
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") + 1 = CTOD("2000-01-02"))
ECHO [CANARY DATE-1 EQ] CURRENT EXPECT .F.:
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") - 1 = CTOD("1999-12-31"))

ECHO ===== DATEADD / DATEDIFF (command + CALC) =====
ECHO [DATEADD cmd] Expect 20000131:
DATEADD 20000101, 30
ECHO [DATEADD cmd] Expect 19991202:
DATEADD 20000101, -30

ECHO [DATEDIFF cmd] Expect 2:
DATEDIFF 20000101, 20000103

CALC DATEADD(DATE(), 30)
CALC DATEDIFF(CTOD("2000-01-01"), DATE())

ECHO ===== CANARIES: RHS EXPRESSIONS IN COMPARISONS =====
ECHO [CANARY RHS-EQ-1] Expect .T.:
CALC (3 = 1 + 2)
ECHO [CANARY RHS-EQ-2] Expect .T.:
CALC ((1 + 2) = (6 / 2))
ECHO [CANARY RHS-EQ-3] Expect .T.:
CALC ((1 + 2 * 3) = (1 + (2 * 3)))

ECHO ===== STRING / CHAR COMMANDS =====
ALLTRIM "  hi  "
LTRIM "  hi"
RTRIM "hi  "
TRIM "hi  "
UPPER "aBc"
LOWER "aBc"
PROPER "joHN"
LEN "ABCDE"
LEFT "ABCDE", 3
RIGHT "ABCDE", 2
SUBSTR "ABCDE", 2, 3
AT "CD", "ABCDE"
ATC "cd", "ABCDE"
CHR 65
ASC "A"
SPACE 3
REPLICATE "x", 5
PADC "hi", 6
PADL "hi", 6
PADR "hi", 6
STUFF "ABCDE", 2, 2, "ZZ"
STR 123
VAL "123.45"
ECHO [CANARY TRANSFORM-ARGS] Expect error (missing 2nd arg):
TRANSFORM 123
LIKE "SMITH", "SMI%"

ECHO ===== NORMALIZE / MULTIREP / CONCAT / STRCAT =====
ECHO [CANARY NORMALIZE-CLI] Expect usage (args required):
NORMALIZE "  a  b  "
ECHO [CANARY MULTIREP-CLI] Expect usage/error until grammar is finalized:
MULTIREP "banana", "a", "A", "n", "N"
CONCAT "A", "B"
CALC CONCAT("A","B")
STRCAT "A", "B"

ECHO ===== TABLES: CORE TABLE/ORDER/CURSOR PROBES =====
ECHO [NOTE] Probe pairs: RECNO before+after LIST/SMARTLIST/WHERE/REINDEX to observe cursor restore behavior.

ECHO ===== BUILDING =====
SELECT BUILDING
AREA
STRUCT
FIELDS
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
DISPLAY
RECORDVIEW
TOP
RECNO
SKIP 1
RECNO
BOTTOM
RECNO
TOP
RECNO

SET ORDER TO BUILDING BLDG
ASCEND
LIST 3
DESCEND
LIST 3
ASCEND

ECHO [NOTE] SET UNIQUE syntax in this build:
SET UNIQUE FIELD BLDG ON
SET UNIQUE FIELD BLDG OFF

SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
LIST 3

ECHO ===== ROOMS =====
SELECT ROOMS
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SKIP 1
BOTTOM
TOP
ECHO [NOTE] ROOMS has ROOMS.cnx present but SET ORDER TO ROOMS failed in run; keep as canary:
SET ORDER TO ROOMS ROOM
LIST 3
SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
LIST 3

ECHO ===== DEPT =====
SELECT DEPT
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SKIP 1
BOTTOM
TOP
SET ORDER TO DEPT DEPT_ID
LIST 3
SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
LIST 3

ECHO ===== MAJORS =====
SELECT MAJORS
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SKIP 1
BOTTOM
TOP
SET ORDER TO MAJORS MAJOR
LIST 3
SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
LIST 3

ECHO ===== TERMS =====
SELECT TERMS
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST ALL
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SKIP 1
BOTTOM
TOP
SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
LIST ALL

ECHO ===== COURSES =====
SELECT COURSES
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SKIP 1
BOTTOM
TOP
ECHO [NOTE] Prior script used "SET ORDER TO CID" which looked for CID.cnx; use table+tag form:
SET ORDER TO COURSES CID
LIST 3
SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
LIST 3

ECHO ===== TEACHERS (INX single-order) =====
SELECT TEACHERS
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SKIP 1
BOTTOM
TOP
FIND LNAME = "WILSON"
SEEK LNAME = "WILSON"
INDEXSEEK "WILSON"

ECHO ===== CLASSES =====
SELECT CLASSES
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SKIP 1
BOTTOM
TOP
SET ORDER TO CLASSES CLS_ID
LIST 3
SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
LIST 3

ECHO ===== STUDENTS (INX single-order) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
STRUCT
COUNT
RECNO
LIST 3
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
RECNO

ECHO ===== LOCATE / FIND / SEEK =====
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "DAVIS"
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
FIND LNAME = "TAYLOR"
TOP
FIND LNAME = "WHITE"
TOP
SEEK LNAME = "DAVIS"
RECNO
TUPLE *
TOP
SEEK FNAME = "ALEX"
RECNO
TUPLE *

ECHO ===== BOOLEAN / PREDICATE GRAMMAR =====
TOP
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
LIST 1
BOOLEAN (GPA > 3)
BOOLEAN (GPA < 3)
BOOLEAN (GPA >= 2 AND GPA <= 4)

ECHO ===== SMARTLIST / WHERE / SETFILTER =====
RECNO
SMARTLIST 5 FOR GPA >= 3.5
RECNO

ECHO [NOTE] WHERE currently doesn't set SHOW FILTER in v9.1; keep as observation:
WHERE GPA >= 3.5
SHOW TABLE
SHOW INDEX

COUNT

SET FILTER TO LNAME = "TAYLOR"
COUNT
SET FILTER TO

ECHO ===== AGGREGATES =====
SUM GPA
AVERAGE GPA
AVG GPA
MIN GPA
MAX GPA

ECHO ===== STUDENTS DATE FIELDS + DATE ALGEBRA =====
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
TUPLE DOB
TUPLE ENROLL_D
CALC DOB
CALC DOB + 1
CALC DOB - 1
CALC DATEADD(DOB, 30)
CALC DATEDIFF(DOB, DATE())
CALC DATE() - DOB

ECHO [CANARY DATEDIFF-SIGN] CURRENT EXPECT .T. (since DATE()-DOB is negative in v9.1):
CALC (DATEDIFF(DOB, DATE()) = -(DATE() - DOB))

ECHO ===== RELATIONS ENGINE =====
REL LIST
REL CLEAR ALL
REL ADD STUDENTS ENROLL ON SID
REL ADD ENROLL CLASSES ON CLS_ID
REL LIST
REL REFRESH
REL_LIST
REL_REFRESH
CMDREL
CMDREL LIST
CMDREL REFRESH

ECHO ===== TUPLE CROSS-AREA =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
TUPLE *
TUPLE LNAME,FNAME
TUPLE #11.*
TUPLE #9.*,#11.LNAME
TUPTALK

ECHO ===== TABLE BUFFER CANARY =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
LIST 1
TUPLE *
TABLE ON
REPLACE FNAME WITH "DeraldNew"
ECHO [CANARY BUF-VIS-1] TUPLE shows buffer immediately:
TUPLE *
ECHO [CANARY BUF-VIS-2] LIST still shows DBF until COMMIT:
LIST 1
COMMIT
ECHO [CANARY BUF-VIS-3] After COMMIT, record order may change if INX rebuild reorders; verify by SEEK/LOCATE:
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
LIST 1

REPLACE FNAME WITH "Derald"
COMMIT
TABLE OFF
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
LIST 1

ECHO ===== CALCWRITE REVERSIBLE WRITE (GPA +/- 0.01) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
TABLE ON
TUPLE GPA
CALC GPA = GPA + 0.01
TUPLE GPA
COMMIT
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
LIST 1
CALC GPA = GPA - 0.01
COMMIT
LOCATE FOR LNAME = "TAYLOR"
LIST 1
TABLE OFF

ECHO ===== INDEX / SETINDEX / REINDEX =====
ECHO [NOTE] Avoid CNX <name> and SETCNX TO ... for now (parser misreads TO).
ECHO [NOTE] SET ORDER TO <table> <tag> is the stable path currently.

SELECT BUILDING
SET ORDER TO BUILDING BLDG
REINDEX
SHOW INDEX

SELECT ROOMS
ECHO [CANARY] ROOMS SET ORDER TO ROOMS currently fails:
SET ORDER TO ROOMS ROOM
SHOW INDEX

SELECT STUDENTS
ECHO [CANARY] SET INDEX requires filename (do not call bare):
* SET INDEX
REINDEX
SHOW INDEX
INDEXSEEK "DAVIS"

ECHO ===== FILE OPS (SAFE, under tmp\) =====
ECHO [NOTE] Keep explicit filenames; avoid wildcard DIR/ERASE in DotTalk.
! cmd /c "echo DotTalkTmpProbe>tmp\dt_probe.txt"
! cmd /c "echo DotTalkTmpProbe2>tmp\dt_probe2.txt"
DIR tmp\dt_probe.txt
DIR tmp\dt_probe2.txt
ERASE tmp\dt_probe.txt
ERASE tmp\dt_probe2.txt
DIR tmp

ECHO ===== SQLITE =====
SQLITE OPEN "tmp\sql_regression.sqlite"
SQLITE EXEC CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS t(x INT);
SQLITE EXEC DELETE FROM t;
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t(x) VALUES (1);
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t(x) VALUES (2);
SQLITE SELECT SELECT * FROM t;
SQLITE CLOSE

ECHO ===== DOTSCRIPT / GO (REAL, NOT USAGE) =====
! cmd /c "echo SET ECHO ON>tmp\mini_regression.dts"
! cmd /c "echo ECHO MINI_DOTSCRIPT_OK>>tmp\mini_regression.dts"
DOTSCRIPT tmp\mini_regression.dts
ECHO GO_OK
GO TOP

ECHO ===== SCRIPTING BLOCKS (SAFE NON-LOOPING) =====
IF .F.
    ECHO IF_BRANCH_RAN_UNEXPECTED
ELSE
    ECHO ELSE_BRANCH_RAN_OK
ENDIF

WHILE .F.
    ECHO WHILE_BODY_RAN_UNEXPECTED
ENDWHILE

UNTIL .T.
    ECHO UNTIL_BODY_RAN_UNEXPECTED
ENDUNTIL

SELECT BUILDING
TOP
SCAN
    TUPLE *
ENDSCAN

ECHO ===== TUPTALK MINI =====
SELECT STUDENTS
TUPTALK RESET
TUPTALK PUSH ALL
TUPTALK PUSH FILTER CND
TUPTALK PUSH 3
TUPTALK PUSH ROW
TUPTALK LIST
TUPTALK NORMALIZE
TUPTALK DUMP
TUPTALK EXPORT CSV students_norm.csv
TUPTALK EXPORT TSV students_norm.tsv

ECHO ===== SQLITE SMOKE (INLINE) =====
SQLITE VERSION
SQLITE OPEN :memory:
SQLITE EXEC CREATE TABLE t (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, n INTEGER);
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t (name, n) VALUES ('alpha', 10);
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t (name, n) VALUES ('bravo', 20);
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t (name, n) VALUES ('charlie', 30);
SQLITE SELECT SELECT id, name, n FROM t ORDER BY id;
SQLITE CLOSE

ECHO ===== MANUAL / DESTRUCTIVE / HANG-RISK =====
ECHO [MANUAL] Interactive/hang-risk:
ECHO   BROWSE / BROWSER / SIMPLEBROWSER / SMARTBROWSER
ECHO   BROWSETUI / BROWSETV / FOXTALK / FOXPRO / TVISION / TURBOPACK
ECHO
ECHO [MANUAL] Destructive ops (do not run in automated regression):
ECHO   DELETE / RECALL / UNDELETE / PACK / ZAP
ECHO
ECHO [MANUAL] Unknown-grammar / environment-dependent:
ECHO   EXPORT / IMPORT / REBUILD / SORT / VALIDATE / TEST / SQLERASE / SHUTDOWN

* NEW Indexing with IMDB open source integration
LMDB

* dbfilenameuppercase.cdx.d
lmdb open indexes/STUDENTS.cdx.d db LNAME
lmdb info
lmdb seek WILSON
lmdb scan A Z
LMDB close

lmdb open indexes/STUDENTS.cdx.d
lmdb use LNAME
lmdb seek ANDERSON
lmdb scan A Z
lmdb close

ECHO ===== CLEAN SHUTDOWN =====
SCHEMAS
SCHEMAS CLOSE
ECHO ===== EXHAUSTIVE FULL REGRESSION END =====
QUIT

$py12 = "D:\code\ccode\build\vcpkg_installed\x64-windows\tools\python3\python.exe"
& $py12 D:\code\ccode\bindings\pydottalk_smoke.py

